                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.20857/2604.20857v1/figs/hierarchical-index.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3.Hierarchical Three-Stage Retrieval Pipeline.The system uses a coarse-to-fine filtering strategy to ensure domain relevance and figure-level specificity.\nStage 1 retrieves candidate papers using a title index to constrain the search space to the target discipline (S1S_{1}).\nStage 2 reranks withinS1S_{1}using an abstract index to retain papers with similar problem settings and methodology (S2S_{2}), aided by a Deep Fetch mechanism to preserve recall under filtering.\nStage 3 performs caption-level matching withinS2S_{2}to retrieve the final figure exemplars aligned with the user’s intended diagram description.",
